---
import RouteDetailLayout from '../layouts/route-detail.astro';
---

<RouteDetailLayout
        title="About | Gunks Climbing Guide"
        bodyClass="font-sans bg-base-100 p-12 text-base-100-content"
>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/"
       class="text-[0.8rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-60 transition-opacity hover:opacity-100">← All
        Routes</a>
    <h1 class="font-yellowtail text-6xl text-pretty">About this Guide</h1>
    <article class="grid gap-6 font-light [&_h2]:mt-2 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:uppercase [&_p]:m-0">
        <div>
            <h2>The Gunks</h2>
            <p>The Shawangunk Mountains — the Gunks — rise above the Hudson Valley in New Paltz, New York. The cliffs
                are made of hard quartzite conglomerate, swept clean by glaciers and eroded into the horizontal crack
                systems and roofs that define the area's climbing.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>This Guide</h2>
            <p>A personal selection of Gunks routes — mostly at the Trapps, the main cliff band — with notes on what
                makes each climb worth doing. Routes range from moderate single-pitch introductions to sustained roof
                problems.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>Getting There</h2>
            <p>The Trapps and Near Trapps are accessed from the Mohonk Preserve. A day pass is required. The carriage
                road trail runs below the cliff and connects all the major buttresses.</p>
        </div>
    </article>
    </div>
</RouteDetailLayout>
